meico.musicxml

Class MusicXml

  • java.lang.Object
    • meico.xml.XmlBase
      • meico.musicxml.MusicXml

  • public class MusicXml
extends XmlBase
    This class represents a MusicXML document. It relies heaily on the framework ProxyMusic.
    Author:
    Axel Berndt

      • toScorePartwise

        public static nu.xom.Document toScorePartwise(nu.xom.Document scoreTimewise)
        ProxyMusic does not support unmarshalling of score-timewise MusicXML. This method is meant to work around this limitation. It converts a score-timewise XML Document to a score-partwise one, so it can be used to create a MusicXml object.
        Parameters:
        scoreTimewise -
        Returns:

      • toScorePartwise

        public MusicXml toScorePartwise()
        Convert this object into a score-partwise representation of the MusicXML. If this is already a score-partwise MusicXML, the result is this. If this is an opus MusicXML, the result is null. Otherwise, the result is a new MusicXml instance with the converted data.
        Returns:
        the result or null

      • toScoreTimewise

        public MusicXml toScoreTimewise()
        Convert this object into a score-timewise representation of the MusicXML. If this is already a score-timewise MusicXML, the result is this. If this is an opus MusicXML, the result is null. Otherwise, the result is a new MusicXml instance with the converted data.
        Returns:
        the result or null

      • setDocument

        public void setDocument(nu.xom.Document document)
        Load and unmarshall a new XML document into this object. This will effectively replace all MusicXML data stored in this object so far. The document itself will not be stored in this object as it will not reflect any editings done afterward on the unmarshalled datastructure. The Document should be of type score-partwise or opus. If it is score-timewise, use the from() factory instead to create a new MusicXml instance.
        Overrides:
        setDocument in class XmlBase
        Parameters:
        document -
